00:00:01.270 --> 00:00:04.570
Adding background music to your movies

00:00:06.150 --> 00:00:09.710
Adding background music to your iMovie project 

00:00:08.730 --> 00:00:12.850
adds excitement and professional polish to your movies.

00:00:12.865 --> 00:00:15.650
Adding a background track is easy

00:00:15.675 --> 00:00:17.700
just click the music and sound 

00:00:17.720 --> 00:00:19.740
effects button underneath the viewer,

00:00:19.761 --> 00:00:23.970
then you will have access to all your songs 

00:00:22.090 --> 00:00:26.080
in iTunes library as well as built in loops and jingles, 

00:00:25.100 --> 00:00:28.190
that come with iMovie 09.

00:00:28.213 --> 00:00:32.160
You can preview any song by just double clicking it.

00:00:32.183 --> 00:00:38.880
♪ Music ♪

00:00:38.895 --> 00:00:41.960
To find that certain song in iTunes library, quickly,

00:00:41.983 --> 00:00:46.560
just type the song name in the search box.

00:00:46.585 --> 00:00:48.690
When you find the song you wanna add,

00:00:48.710 --> 00:00:51.180
drag it to grey space in the project window,

00:00:51.201 --> 00:00:54.520
making sure not to drop on to a clip.

00:00:54.543 --> 00:00:56.460
Green highlight show where 

00:00:56.480 --> 00:00:58.400
the background music starts and ends.

00:00:58.418 --> 00:01:00.480
If the music is longer than your movie,

00:01:00.501 --> 00:01:04.700
The music will just fade out of the end of it.

00:01:04.715 --> 00:01:09.570
♪ Music fading out ♪

00:01:09.593 --> 00:01:11.750
If your movie is longer than your song,

00:01:11.773 --> 00:01:14.820
you can easily add an another song, 

00:01:13.840 --> 00:01:15.900
by dragging it to the grey space in your project.

00:01:17.916 --> 00:01:19.610
If you wanna have the background music 

00:01:19.630 --> 00:01:21.320
start playing later in your movie,

00:01:21.335 --> 00:01:28.240
just drag the music to where you want it to start.

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:31.350
♪ Music ♪

00:01:31.371 --> 00:01:32.500
The highlight turns purple to show that

00:01:32.920 --> 00:01:35.950
the music is pinned to a specific clip,

00:01:35.968 --> 00:01:37.680
now if you move the clip,

00:01:37.698 --> 00:01:40.860
the music will move with it.

00:01:40.876 --> 00:01:43.240
To make the background music louder and softer,

00:01:43.258 --> 00:01:44.370
just double click it,

00:01:44.388 --> 00:01:51.150
then dragg the volume slide untill it just right.

00:01:51.166 --> 00:01:52.530
With the background track,

00:01:52.548 --> 00:01:55.030
you can add feeling and style to your movies,

00:01:55.055 --> 00:01:58.750
making them more fun to watch and share.

00:01:58.771 --> 00:02:05.750
♪ Music ♪ 

